quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  38,27,"And in no way have We created the heaven and the earth and whatever is between them untruthfully. That is the surmise of the ones who have disbelieved. So woe to the ones who have disbelieved, from the Fire"
  38,28,"Or even shall We make the ones who have believed and done deeds of righteousness as the corruptors in the earth, or even shall We make the pious as the constantly impious"
  38,29,"A Book We have sent down to you, Blessed, that they may ponder over its ayat (Verses, signs) and that men endowed with intellects would remind themselves"
  38,30,And We bestowed on Dawud (David) Sulayman; (Solomon) how excellent a bondman he was! Surely he was a constant resorter (to Us)
  38,31,"As there were set (in parade) before him at nightfall light-footed (Literally: standing on three feet) coursers"
  38,32,"Then he said, \"Surely I have loved the love of (earthly) charitable (things) better than the Remembrance of my Lord, \" until (the sun) disappeared behind the curtain (Literally: made herself disappear with the curtain)"
  38,33,"Turn them back to me!\" Then he took to striking (Or: slashing) their shanks and necks"
  38,34,"And indeed We already tempted Sulayman, (Solomon) and We cast upon his chair a corporeal (form); thereafter he turned penitent"
  38,35,"He said, \"Lord! Forgive me, and bestow on me a kingdom such as may not behoove anyone even after me; surely You, Ever You, are The Superb Bestower"
  38,36,"So We subjected to him the wind, which ran at his command, gently where he would direct it light on"
  38,37,"And Ash-Shayatin, (The ever-vicious \"one\", i.e., the Devils) every skilled builder, and (expert) diver"
  38,38,And others interlinked in fetters
  38,39,This is Our gift; so be bounteous or hold back without reckoning
  38,40,And surely he has indeed in Our Providence a near proximity and a fair resorting
  38,41,"And remember Our bondman Ayyub, (Job) as he called out to his Lord (saying), \"Ash-Shaytan (The ever-vicious \"one\", i.e., the Devil) has touched me with calamity and torment"
  38,42,"Scamper with your leg. This is a washing-place, cool and a drink"